rComments: He's a great professor.  He teaches at UNL now, but I know he used to teach at Illinois.  He's very passionate in teaching about Spanish culture and very kind.

He's so nice! I still learned a lot in class even though it was fairly easy. Do go to class though because the final and some of the quizzes are based off of what you talk about in class as well as the readings.
great teacher... great class... enough said

Very fun and has lots of jokes, a very real teacher who cares.  He likes to make class interesting and you need to be lively in order to have fun.  Be prepared to speak spanish a lot and have fun at the same time.  The only hard part is doing the 10 minute oral presentations.  I enjoyed his class!
